.TH "hvc_iucv_dtr_rts" 9 "hvc_iucv_dtr_rts" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hvc_iucv_dtr_rts \- HVC notifier for handling DTR/RTS
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" hvc_iucv_dtr_rts
.BI "(struct hvc_struct *hp "  ","
.BI "int raise "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hp" 12
Pointer the HVC device (struct hvc_struct)
.IP "raise" 12
Non-zero to raise or zero to lower DTR/RTS lines
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine notifies the HVC back-end to raise or lower DTR/RTS
lines.  Raising DTR/RTS is ignored.  Lowering DTR/RTS indicates to
drop the IUCV connection (similar to hang up the modem).
